12/08/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Chief of Army General Staff Nikola Kolev and his visiting counterpart, Metodi Stamboliski, discussed possibilities Monday (11 August) for enhancing bilateral co-operation. They agreed joint military exercises and training would be of huge benefit to both armies.
In other news Monday, a police official announced plans to open three new crossings at the Macedonian-Albanian border near Trebiste, Miresi and Korab. The new crossings would facilitate police efforts to limit trans-border crime and illegal crossings. (MIA, Makfax- 11/08/03)
